Human Organ System Disease Ontology
Circulatory System:
  • heart, blood vessels, blood
Lymphatic system:
  • lymph nodes and vessels, tonsils, thymus, spleen, lymph, bone marrow
Digestive System:
  • Primary organs: mouth, stomach, small Intestine, rectum, colon, gall bladder, salivary gland
  • Accessory organs: teeth, tongue, liver, pancreas, esophagus
Endocrine System:
  • pituitary gland, pineal gland, hypothalamus, thyroid gland, parathyroid gland, adrenal gland
Integumentory System:
  • skin, nails, hair, sweat gland
Muscle System:
  • muscles
 Nervous System:
  • brain, spinal cord, nerves, ganglia, ears, eyes
Reproductive system:
  • Male: testis, Scrotum, penis, vas deferens, prostrate
  • Female: breast, cervix, ovary, uterus, vagina, mammary gland
Repiratory System:
  • lungs, nose, trachea, larynx, pharynx, bronchi
Skeletal system:
  • bones, joints, ligaments, cartilage
Excretory/Urinary System:
  • kidneys, bladder, uretha, ureters,
Embryonic System:
  • amnion, umbilical cord, embryo, placenta
Other organ system:
  • adipose tissue peritoneum leiomios
